ry. However, there's a risk that existing logging may affect future tests due to the special initialization detection. It feels complicated, and I’m still figuring out the best approach!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering FactoryFinder effects**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the potential impacts of `FactoryFinder`, especially when the current context is non-null, which could lead to issues later. It seems there’s no public reset option except for the release, which only resets under specific conditions. Maybe I could create a non-null `FacesContext` before the release to avoid side effects, but that feels complicated. Alternatively, using a separate thread could help, although managing the logging flags on the static cache could get tricky. Lots to consider here!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test logic and thread usage**\\n\\nI need to check the maximum line length, probably around 160 characters, which seems reasonable. I’m wondering if I should generate a count of tests. But does the call to FacesContext.getCurrentInstance affect this if there's already a current instance on the same thread? JUnit often reuses the same thread, but tests do close. To be safe, I could use a new thread without any active ThreadLocal. Though, would the Field#get class initialization happen in the new thread? If the factory isn't initialized, it creates a tricky situation.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Refining test logic for independence**\\n\\nI’m contemplating whether we really need this step. Active call sites are in the constructor, and if this test's assertion detects a non-null current instance from leftovers, it means FactoryFinder might not be called, which could lead to assertion failures. If there’s no assertion? Well, we can’t just ignore null checks. To make this test meaningful, I think using a new thread can help. It might be better to run it in a single-threaded executor, set the TCCL, and call it that way. That should eliminate any ThreadLocal concerns.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying threading approach**\\n\\nI'm considering the threading situation, figuring out that creating a new thread is tricky due to the current context. It seems like the class loader might return some context, but my factory map is empty. That's a relief, but I need to ensure I close the executor properly. A straightforward thread with a join could work, but I should definitely handle exceptions. Using ExecutorService is more idiomatic, so I’ll add a Future and test it with a timeout under 60 seconds. Time to edit!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_wAjVE4az1iW49Sl3AZOIuUlc|fc_01c5c6bbe2b8f4d9016a01f3b922c48192b4a20d62f99e1e39", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/ServletContextFacesContextFactoryTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ServletContextFacesContextFactoryTest {\n    @Test\n    void currentInstanceUsesServletContextAwareFactoryLookupWhenNoFacesContextIsActive() {\n        ClassLoader previousContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(ServletContextFacesContextFactoryTest.class.getClassLoader());\n\n            FacesContext currentInstance = FacesContext.getCurrentInstance();\n\n            assertThat(currentInstance).isNull();\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(previousContextClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;\nimport java.util.concurrent.Executors;\nimport java.util.concurrent.Future;\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\n\nimport jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ServletContextFacesContextFactoryTest {\n    @Test\n    void currentInstanceUsesServletContextAwareFactoryLookupWhenNoFacesContextIsActive() throws Exception {\n        ExecutorService executor = Executors.newSingleThreadExecutor();\n        try {\n            Future<FacesContext> currentInstance = executor.submit(() -> {\n                Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(ServletContextFacesContextFactoryTest.class.getClassLoader());\n                return FacesContext.getCurrentInstance();\n            });\n\n            assertThat(currentInstance.get(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isNull();\n        } finally {\n            executor.shutdownNow();\n            assertThat(executor.awaitTermination(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1297, "output": 1537, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35602, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778512801447, "responseId": "resp_01c5c6bbe2b8f4d9016a01f3a217188192810ec087c46698ad"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_wAjVE4az1iW49Sl3AZOIuUlc|fc_01c5c6bbe2b8f4d9016a01f3b922c48192b4a20d62f99e1e39", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/ServletContextFacesContextFactoryTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "    ...\n  7 package jakarta_platform.jakarta_jakartaee_api;\n  8 \n  9 import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n 10 \n+11 import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;\n+12 import java.util.concurrent.Executors;\n+13 import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n+14 import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\n+15 \n 11 import jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\n 12 \n 13 import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n 14 \n 15 public class ServletContextFacesContextFactoryTest {\n